The paper deals with the formal verification of self-assembling systems, which involves the use of logic and algorithms to ensure the correctness of these systems. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including multi-agent systems (cs.MA), logic in computer science (cs.LO), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and control systems (cs.SY). However, given the focus on formal verification and model checking, cs.MA and cs.SY are less likely than the other three categories.
